Subject: [PATCH 963/974] From 592ef45c05e9786c6094350f536e0770d634110f Mon Sep
 17 00:00:00 2001 From: Taras Kondratiuk <takondra@cisco.com> Date: Wed, 10
 Jun 2015 10:49:50 -0700 Subject: [PATCH 4/6] MIPS: OCTEON: disable watchdog
 before CPU is stopped

When stop_this_cpu() puts CPU offline its watchdog should be
disabled to prevent unnecessary reboot.

Change-Id: I781f2a9ef5e661e1ab4139fe9bbba16b33204952
Bug-Id: CSCuu82009
Signed-off-by: Chandrakala Chavva <cchavva@caviumnetworks.com>
[Original patch taken from Cavium SDK 3.1.2-568]
Signed-off-by: Quanyang Wang <quanyang.wang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/cavium-octeon/smp.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/smp.c b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/smp.c
index 2d7dee4..d4def24 100644
--- a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/smp.c
+++ b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/smp.c
@@ -55,7 +55,7 @@ static octeon_message_fn_t  octeon_message_functions[8] = {
 #endif
 };
 
-static  int octeon_message_free_mask = IS_ENABLED(KEXEC) ? 0xf0 : 0xf8;
+static  int octeon_message_free_mask = IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_KEXEC) ? 0xf0 : 0xf8;
 static DEFINE_SPINLOCK(octeon_message_functions_lock);
 
 int octeon_request_ipi_handler(octeon_message_fn_t fn)
